  "notes": "Modern European Portuguese (PT-PT). Base mapping uses a neutral orthographic standard. Digraphs per Acordo Ortográfico. Portuguese preserves the /v/~/b/ distinction (unique in Ibero-Romance — Castilian merged them). Nasal vowels and extreme vowel reduction are diagnostic features.",
